<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Public accountability and systems engineering journey."
	pubDate={new Date('July 01 2026')}
	status="SYS // ENG"
>
	<p>
		I am <strong>Siddhant</strong>. I designed and built this website as a minimalist, high-signal public accountability dashboard for systems engineering.
	</p>

	<p>
		My core focus is mastering low-level software engineering, hardware memory models, high-performance concurrency, and memory safety without garbage collection. Currently, I am studying the <strong>KAIST Concurrency Course</strong> alongside the interactive edition of the <strong>Brown University Rust Book</strong>.
	</p>

	<p>
		By keeping my coursework goals, daily sprint action items, and technical notes public, I maintain extreme discipline and consistency. Whether writing lock-free data structures, debugging borrow checker rules, or analyzing atomic operations, everything is documented in the open.
	</p>

	<p style="margin-top: 2rem;">
		Explore my daily sprint progress in <a href="/diary">Diary & Tasks</a> or read my technical deep-dives in the <a href="/blog">Blog</a>.
	</p>
</Layout>
